## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 0 |
| **Medium** | 2 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (achieving high line coverage) but almost nothing meaningful is verified. Production bugs slip through because these tests cannot fail even when the code is wrong.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The entire class follows the same pattern: call the method, assert nothing (or only `IsNotNull`). This inflates coverage metrics without verifying behavior.

---

#### 2. No Assertion — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17–21)

Calls `AddProduct` but never verifies the product was stored.

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

---

#### 3. No Assertion — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 31–36)

Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price actually changed.

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesPriceOfExistingProduct()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}
```

---

#### 4. No Assertion — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38–43)

Never verifies the product was actually removed.

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_DeletesProductFromCatalog()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}
```

---

#### 5. No Assertion — `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63–66)

Calls `GetProductCount()` and discards the result entirely.

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetProductCount_ReturnsNumberOfStoredProducts()
{
    Assert.AreEqual(0, _catalog.GetProductCount());
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
}
